window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>War! The Kingdom of Penn and the Queendom of Georgia have reignited their centuries-long feud for control of the New World.</b></p> <p>All along the frontline, the forces of Penn have faltered and been pushed back. Only Rhett Allen in the small hamlet of South Boston stood his ground. Even better, he won. With the Georgian vanguard defeated and the heir to the Georgian throne in his custody, he's offered hope to a nation mired in defeat.</p> <p>But standing his ground won't be enough to win this war. To make use of the new prisoner, he must get her to Philadelphia where the King and his court can leverage her capture to shift the tides of battle in their favor.</p> <p>Too bad Rhett and company are almost surrounded, and getting all the way from Southern Virginia to Pennsylvania is no picnic. Rhett has a disgraced Lord General coming for revenge and incompetence within his own ranks to deal with. Then, there is the whole matter of how his unborn child with the Summer Ambassador threatens the balance of power among the Sidhe of the Tuatha DÃ© Danann. Autumn is on the hunt, and she will not stop, no matter what country Rhett is in.</p> <p>With all of these forces aligned against him, it will take all of Rhett's new power and old, Thirdborn cunning to complete his mission and ensure Penn's victory.</p> <p><i>Narrated in duet style.</i></p>"; 
